comment.shortText: Downloads the given array of bots as a `.aux` or a `.pdf` file with the given filename. Useful for quickly backing up a set of bots.
comment.text:
The downloaded bots will be stored in the Version 1 format of the [AUX File Format](glossary:aux), which is well suited for most scenarios.
For scenarios where you want conflict-free initialization of a shared inst, you should use [`os.downloadBotsAsInitialzationUpdate(bots, filename)`](ref:os.downloadBotsAsInitialzationUpdate).

tags.text:
Download all the bots in the "abc" dimension as "abcBots.aux".
os.downloadBots(getBots(inDimension("abc")), "abcBots");

Download the current bot as "currentBot.aux".
os.downloadBots([bot], "currentBot");

comment.shortText: the array of bots that should be downloaded.

the name of the file that the bots should be stored in. If the filename ends with `.pdf`, then a PDF file will be downloaded with the bots as embedded data. Otherwise, `.aux` will automatically be added to the end of the filename.

comment.shortText: Downloads the given array of bots as a `.aux` or a `.pdf` file with the given filename.
comment.text:
The downloaded bots will be stored in the Version 2 format of the [AUX File Format](glossary:aux), which is better suited towards scenarios which require conflict-free initialization of a shared inst from the AUX file.
For an archive of the current state, you should use [`os.downloadBots(bots, filename)`](ref:os.downloadBots) which is better for scenarios which require direct access to the bot data.

comment.shortText: Downloads all of the shared bots into a `.aux` file on the player's computer. The file will have the same name as the inst.
comment.text: Note that this function is almost exactly the same as [`os.downloadBots(bots, filename)`](ref:os.downloadBots). The only difference is that all bots in the shared space are included and the file is named for you automatically.

comment.shortText:
Parses a list of bot mods from the given string of data.
The data can be JSON or the contents of a PDF file.
Returns an array of mods where each mod has the structure of a bot (i.e. it has `id` and `tags` properties).
Returns `null` if the data is not valid JSON or PDF.

comment.shortText: Imports an AUX file from the given string.
comment.text:
If the string contains JSON, then the JSON will be imported as if it was a .aux file. If the string is a [URL](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/URL), then it will be downloaded and imported.

This is useful to quickly download a AUX file and load it into the current inst from a site such as https://gist.github.com/.
